			<div class="col-md-7 column">
				<h3> About Us </h3> <br>
					<p> Westown Farm Allotments is run by Simon Kenny and his wife Ruth. The Allotments began as a college business project in the winter of 2009. 
					GIY (Grow it yourself) had become hugely trendy and Simon recognised that there was a gap in the local market. 
					He established the allotments in the spring of 2010 and has been running them successfully ever since.</p> <br>
					<p> Both Simon and Ruth have a huge interest in living a self sustainable life. They currently live in their Yurt with their dog "Loki" and cat "Kenobi". They have installed a solar panel for power.
					They grow their own vegetables in their polytunnel and intend to one day build an environmentally friendly Cob House. </p> <br>
					<p> They plan on expanding the allotments to include an orchard that will be planted this year. </p> <br>
					<p> Simon has his own successful Youtube channel where he posts various instructional videos on how to make useful tools and general farm life. </p> <br>	
					<p> We have also recently set up our <a href = "https://twitter.com/wfallotments">Twitter</a> account. Make sure you follow us for any announcements!</p>
			</div>
			
